  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Audio Player Code**\n\nI\'m now diving into the `AudioPlayer.tsx` component. I see imports for `TRACKS` from `../data` and `studioSynth` from `../lib/synth`. Further exploration of the components seems necessary to understand the core interactions. I\'m focusing on how these components contribute to the audio playback.\n\n\n**Defining Component States**\n\nI\'ve outlined several state variables for the audio player component. I\'ll maintain states for lists of tracks and active tracks. Stems will be controlled via boolean states for drums, bass, lead, and space. There will also be a state to control whether the audio is `isPlaying` or not, and track the `bpm` and `currentStep` from the synthesizer. I\'m focusing next on mouse interaction on the XY Pad; calculating coordinates from clicks and drags, keeping coordinates in percent and calling the synthesizer\'s `updateXYFilter` based on these values. Finally, I\'ll add a canvas for audio wave visualizations, drawing using data from `studioSynth.getAnalyser()` with a `requestAnimationFrame` loop.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will build the core interactive element of the portfolio, the `/src/components/AudioPlayer.tsx` component. This component acts as a high-fidelity mixing console and Ableton-esque synthesizer workspace. It features:\n- **Modular Multi-Track Selector**: Seamlessly jump between Cyberpunk, Ambient, and Retro tracks.\n- **Stem Equalizer Dashboard**: 4 toggle buttons represent stems: Drums, sub-bass, lead synths, and spatial micro-delays.\n- **Dynamic 16-Step Sequencer Grid**: An on-screen running indicator that lights up in sync with the real synthesizer beats!\n- **Interactive X-Y Filter Morph Pad**: A tactile controller where dragging the mouse bends the resonance and cutoff frequency of the oscillator live.\n- **Real-Time Spectrogram Visualizer**: A 100% real Canvas visualizer that polls the Web Audio API or smoothly simulates cinematic waveforms when idle."
    thinking_duration {
